parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brakes to overheat, lock up, or fail to release, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, or even fires.
symptoms: The brakes overheat
the brakes lock up
the brake pedal extends to the floor
the ABS warning light comes on
the vehicle pulls to one side
the brakes take longer to stop
the vehicle catches on fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake calipers can cause the brakes to overheat, stick, or fail to release, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, or even fires.
symptoms: The brake calipers overheat
the brake calipers stick
the brake pedal extends to the floor
the ABS warning light comes on
the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake fluid system can cause the brakes to overheat, lock up, or fail to release, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, or even fires.
symptoms: The brake fluid overheats
the brake fluid leaks
the brake pedal extends to the floor
the ABS warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A chafed wire in the engine compartment can cause engine failure, stalling, and even fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine stalling while driving
smoke coming from the engine compartment
blown fuses (specifically the PCM/TCM fuse)
engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Line Leak above Fuel Tank
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel line leak above the fuel tank can cause fuel to spill onto the road or surrounding area, increasing the risk of a fire or explosion, which can lead to serious injury or fatalities.
symptoms: Fuel leaking from the fuel line above the fuel tank
fuel smell or odor
fuel droplets or puddles on the ground near the fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked fuel tank can cause fuel to leak out, increasing the risk of a fire or explosion, which can lead to serious injury or fatalities.
symptoms: Fuel leaking from the fuel tank
fuel smell or odor
fuel droplets or puddles on the ground near the fuel tank
visible cracks or damage on the fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Windshield Angle Causing Glare in Rear View Mirror
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unique angle of the front windshield can cause sunlight to reflect onto the windshield, resulting in glare in the exterior rear view mirror, which can reduce or eliminate visibility, increasing the risk of accidents or collisions.
symptoms: Sunlight reflection on the windshield causes glare in the exterior rear view mirror
poor or no visibility in the rear view mirror
difficulty seeing traffic or obstacles behind the vehicle.
